intro: Acinodendron multiplinerve, commonly known as the multi-nerved acinodendron, is a flowering plant belonging to the Rubiaceae family. It is characterized by its compound leaves with multiple nerves, giving it its scientific name. The plant produces small, clustered flowers that are typically white or pale yellow. It is native to tropical regions of Africa and is often found in moist, shaded environments. Due to its unique morphology and limited distribution, it is of interest to botanists and conservationists.
